[assistant] Fixed the runtime failure by avoiding reliance on a fully started Hadoop `HttpServer`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated `RouterTest` so it:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Still uses the public `WebApps`/`WebApp` API to initialize the web app host class.
[assistant] - Catches the JDK security-manager-related `UnsupportedOperationException` from Hadoop’s `UserGroupInformation`.
[assistant] - Then directly invokes `webApp.setup()` after the host class has been initialized, which reaches:
[assistant]   - `Router.addController(...)` → `Class#getMethod(...)`
[assistant]   - `Router.load(...)` → `Class#forName(...)`
[assistant] - Only calls `webApp.stop()` if the embedded server actually started.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated file:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - `tests/src/org.apache.hadoop/hadoop-yarn-common/2.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_hadoop/hadoop_yarn_common/RouterTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] The `hadoop-common` test dependency remains necessary because `WebApps` depends on Hadoop common classes at runtime.
[assistant-event] text_end
